'''Gebran Bassil''' ({{lang-ar|Ø¬Ø¨Ø±Ø§Ù Ø¨Ø§Ø³ÙÙ Ø¬Ø¨Ø±Ø§Ù}}) is a Lebanese politician,he is also a member of the [[March 8 Alliance]]-backed [[Free Patriotic Movement]]. Owing to his immense qualifications(he is the son-in-law of the leader of the Free Patriotic Movement [[Michel Aoun]]) he served as the Minister of Telecommunications in the Lebanese cabinet from May 2008 to June 2009, and then served as Minister of Energy in the [[Lebanese government of November 2009|government]] headed by [[Saad Hariri]] before he issued the statement that March 8 would quit the government. He is now the [[Lebanon|Lebanese]] [[Minister (government)|Minister]] of [[Energy]] in the [[Lebanese government of November 2011|second government]] headed by [[Najib Mikati]].<ref>{{Citation | magazine = The Lebanese Presidency | url = http://www.presidency.gov.lb/PhotoGallery/Pages/NewsDetails.aspx?NewsRef=3077 |accessdate=November 11, 2009}}</ref>
